p and S-corporation analysis for equity partner K-1 partnership distributions with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks at the partnership level for firm-level depreciation and amortization, B3-3.3-02 self-employed Schedule C analysis with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks for solo practitioners, B3-3.1-09 other sources of income for in-house counsel RSU vesting analysis with continuing schedule documentation. Conventional Conforming, Conventional Jumbo, Conventional Super-Jumbo, S-Corp Self-Employed, Schedule C + Form 1084, Bank Statement Non-QM, Asset-Depletion Non-QM (post-settlement plaintiff), and in-house counsel multi-source aggregation loan program options. Legal services is Specified Service Trade or Business (SSTB) under IRC Section 199A with QBI deduction phase-out at higher income. AmLaw 100 and 200 ranking and revenue tiers context, law firm M&amp;A consolidation activity, Cravath scale wage competition driving BigLaw associate compensation arms race, ALSP (Alternative Legal Service Providers) industry disruption, lateral partner market activity, and in-house counsel migration trend from BigLaw partnership to public company General Counsel." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/attorneys/">
